criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients with histologically confirmed squamous cell esophageal cancer, without any
             previous anti-tumor therapy;

          2. Preoperative clinical TNM stage：cT1b-3N0-1M0;

          3. Adequate cardiopulmonary, liver, brain and kidney functions for esophagectomy either
             via right thoracotomy or VATS;

          4. No evidence of suspicious neck lymph node metastasis (LN short diameter < 0.8cm or LN
             short/long diameter <0.65 by cervical CT and/or ultrasound);

          5. Willing to participate the clinical trial and sign the informed consent before being
             enrolled into clinical trail

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Previous use of anti-cancer therapy;

          2. Preoperative clinical TNM stage: N2-3 or M1;

          3. Inadequate cardiopulmonary,liver, brain and kidney function for surgery;

          4. Previous malignancy history.

          5. Suspicious neck lymph node metastasis (LN short diameter ≧0.8cm or LN short/long
             diameter ≧0.65 by cervical CT and/or ultrasound);

          6. Unwilling to participate the clinical trial and refuse to sign informed consent.
